    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it doesn't feel like a \"symptom\". it feels like a realization. like i finally saw behind the curtain. if it's just my brain making up this whole mess to protect me, then why is it so much more logical to believe the world is fake than to believe it's real? why would my brain create an entire universe of suffering just to \"protect\" me? it feels more like the noise is just a mistake that needs to be corrected.",
